Aggrobot_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP Dizzy. FIRE to send Dizzy soaring forward through the air. Dizzy charges then unleashes plasma blasts at enemies in line of sight. Enemies hit by her plasma are Blinded. When Dizzy expires she reverts into a dormant globule. INTERACT to reclaim the globule and gain another Dizzy charge after a short cooldown.
Aggrobot_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: EQUIP Mosh. FIRE to throw Mosh like a grenade. ALT FIRE to lob. Upon landing Mosh duplicates across a large area that deals a small amount of damage over time then after a short delay explodes.
Aggrobot_Strings.Ultimate_Description: EQUIP Thrash. FIRE to link with Thrash’s mind and steer her through enemy territory. ACTIVATE to lunge forward and explode, Detaining any players in a small radius. When Thrash expires she reverts into a dormant globule. INTERACT to reclaim the globule and gain another Thrash charge after a short cooldown. Thrash can be reclaimed once.
Aggrobot_Strings.Ability1_Description: EQUIP Wingman. FIRE to send Wingman forward seeking enemies. Wingman unleashes a concussive blast toward the first enemy he sees. ALT FIRE when targeting a Spike site or planted Spike to have Wingman defuse or plant the Spike. To plant, Gekko must have the Spike in his inventory. When Wingman expires he reverts into a dormant globule. INTERACT to reclaim the globule and gain another Wingman charge after a short cooldown.
Aggrobot_Strings.Description: Gekko the Angeleno leads a tight-knit crew of calamitous creatures. His buddies bound forward, scattering enemies out of the way, with Gekko chasing them down to regroup and go again.

BountyHunter_Strings.Ability_Q_Description: EQUIP a knot of raw fear. FIRE to throw. The knot drops down after a set time. RE-USE to drop the knot early. The knot ruptures on impact, holding nearby enemies in place. Held enemies are Deafened, and Decayed.
BountyHunter_Strings.Ability_4_Description: EQUIP a prowler. FIRE to send the prowler forward. HOLD FIRE to steer the prowler towards your crosshair. The prowler will chase down the first enemy or terror trail it sees, and Nearsight the enemy on impact.
BountyHunter_Strings.Ability_X_Description: EQUIP the power of nightmare itself. FIRE to unleash a wave of unstoppable nightmare energy. Enemies caught in the wave are Marked by terror trails, Deafened, and Decayed.
BountyHunter_Strings.Description: Turkish bounty hunter Fade unleashes the power of raw nightmare to seize enemy secrets. Attuned with terror itself, she hunts down targets and reveals their deepest fears - before crushing them in the dark.

Breach_Strings.Ultimate_Description: EQUIP a Seismic Charge. FIRE to send a cascading quake through all terrain in a large cone. The quake Concusses and knocks up anyone caught in it.
Breach_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: EQUIP a fusion charge. FIRE the charge to set a slow-acting burst through the wall. The burst does heavy damage to anyone caught in its area.
Breach_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a seismic blast. HOLD FIRE to increase the distance. RELEASE to set off the quake, Concussing all players in its zone and in a line up to the zone.
Breach_Strings.Description: The bionic Swede Breach fires powerful, targeted kinetic blasts to aggressively clear a path through enemy ground. The damage and disruption he inflicts ensures no fight is ever fair.

Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_13_Body:
AUTOMATED EVACUATION ORDER // THIS IS NOT A DRILL
All personnel must evacuate immediately. Report to designated rally points. Failure of Large Radian Collider detected. Variable time acceleration possible. Do not enter Collider areas. Evacuate immediately.
AUTOMATED EVACUATION ORDER // THIS IS NOT A DRILL
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_Ziplines_body:
After a recent tragedy resulting in the fatality of 5 of our Everett-Linde personnel, we are taking a moment to remind everyone that ziplines are for SINGLE RIDERS ONLY. Your safety is our top priority, but in order to ensure it, safety regulations must be adhered to.

K-SEC TEAM
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_8_Body:
Did you get called into security too? I was worried it was something we did, but turns out our chief engineer has gone missing. Relief and worry all at once! This place feels cursed sometimes... 
- Oran
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_5_Body:
Hearing about your world was incredible! I can't believe you have a city-wide geo dome... Truly a modern wonder.
- Oran

ps - Did you see "tie guy?" He gave me a business card that looks more expensive than my whole wardrobe.
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_10_Body:
Hello Mr. Pontes,
Your biometrics screening came back from the central office. I'm happy to confirm it's all clear. You will receive a digital passport that you can use for your trip home after T-0 DAY. Have a safe trip and please ensure you adhere to all protocols. 
- Dr.Santos
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_2_Body:
Hello Rúben, 
Did you finish your initial analysis on the Radian Collider today? I'm confident in our math and I know I'm being paranoid, but I really want to double check everything. Would you mind doing another walkthrough of the Eastern support structure with me tomorrow? 
- Oran McEneff
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_9_Body:
Hello, 
This is an automated response as I am currently on routine furlough. My return date is T-171. Please contact Alpha's Oran McEneff for emergent engineering needs. 
- Rúben Pontes
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_4_Body:
Hey Oran, 
Good thing we double checked! Avoided what could have been a major setback. Maybe the higher ups are finally starting to understand the necessity of teamwork, because I just got security approval for us to work in the core together at the same time! All these segregation rules seem so silly... 
- Rúben
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_3_Body:
Hi Uncle Rúben!
I know you can't get messages right now because "top secret saving the world blah blah whatever," so you probably won't even see this until you're already home, but my soccer team made playoffs! Tidal forecast says we might even get to open the geo-dome for the matches ^^
I'll score a goal for you.
~ Aurora <3
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_11_Body:
I can't believe the day's finally here! There's even a cross-team party on the observation deck after. Meeting in public and not getting chewed out by K-Sec? Novel! Snark aside, it really is happening! The good this will do both our homes is beyond anything I could have hoped for.
- Rúben
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_12_Body: I haven't been this excited for a project launch since... ever? I know it's cliche, but this really is bigger than any one of us. This is hope for generations to come. Looking forward to raising a glass with you tomorrow!
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_6_Body:
Maybe someday I could show you in person (We can dream, right?). Your home sounds beautiful as well though. I can't believe how different things have become just since First Light. Makes me wonder what could have been... But, that's why we're here, right? To build worlds worth living in.
- Rúben
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_7_Body:
Oran McEneff - 
Please report for mandatory security screening at 0700 tomorrow. Prioritize this over any existing engagements. 

K-SEC TEAM
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_14_Body:
This is an auto-generated message. Do not reply.
Due to a site-wide failure, all archives are scheduled for purging tomorrow at 1200 hours. Please backup necessary files. 
- System Admin
Canyon_Journal_StringTable.Canyon_Email_1_Body:
Welcome Oran McEneff to Everett-Linde. Tomorrow at 0900, you are to meet your Omega partner, Rúben Pontes, outside 07/a . As you will be working closely with someone from Omega Kingdom, please ensure all security guidance is strictly adhered to. 

K-SEC TEAM

EsportsHub_Strings.Teams_LandingOverview: International Leagues are the premiere level of competitive play in the VALORANT Champions Tour. These leagues, featuring the world's best players and leading organizations, occur live in-person in studios around the world. They serve as qualifiers for global events like Masters and Champions, fostering rivalries and uniting diverse communities through top-level play.

EsportsHub_Strings.Standings_FirstPlaceDescription: Teams from Alpha and Omega group advance directly to Upper Bracket Semifinals
EsportsHub_Strings.Standings_SecondThirdPlaceDescription: Teams from Alpha and Omega group advance to Upper Bracket Quaterfinals
EsportsHub_Strings.EventBlurb_MastersTwo: The VCT is heading to Shanghai for the second international stop of the 2024 season. With 12 teams representing VCT Americas, VCT EMEA, VCT Pacific, and VCT CN, this event promises to be thrilling! Here is everything you need to know about VALORANT Masters Shanghai, taking place May 23 - June 9.
EsportsHub_Strings.Leagues_Info_CN: The newest International League, VCT CN, will officially start in 2024! This season, 10 partnered teams and one new ascension team will compete live on the VCT CN stage, located in Shanghai, China. They’ll chase the title of VCT CN champion as well as opportunities to make their mark on the global stage!
EsportsHub_Strings.EventBlurb_MastersOne: VALORANT Masters has landed in Madrid! Eight teams from around the world face off in the first international event of the VALORANT Champions Tour 2024. Tune in and watch and see how we do things A NUESTRA MANERA (OUR WAY)!
EsportsHub_Strings.Leagues_Info_Americas: VCT AMERICAS is where you come to hear big talk, see big plays, and follow the big personalities. You’ll see some burn bright and others burn out, but you won’t be able to look away. Located in the entertainment capital of the world, VCT AMERICAS and its 10 partnered teams and one ascended team from across North America, Brazil, and Latin America call Riot Games Arena in Los Angeles home. As the reigning VALORANT World Champion, it's never just a competition; it's a lifestyle.
EsportsHub_Strings.Leagues_Info_EMEA: VCT EMEA is the ultimate showdown of the best teams the region has to offer. A total of 10 partnered teams and one ascended team from Challengers, meeting head-to-head in Berlin. Who will claw and scrape their way to the top to claim their title as VCT EMEA champions?
EsportsHub_Strings.Leagues_Info_Pacific: VCT PACIFIC is a league known for fast play, underdogs, and consistency. Among these 10 partnered teams and one new ascension team, there’s a constant strain between chaos and control. In the 2024 season, watch again as fast paced action clashes against methodical execution.

Grenadier_Strings.Ability1_Description: EQUIP a flash grenade. FIRE to overhand throw. ALT FIRE to lob a weaker version that explodes quickly. The flash grenade explodes after a short fuse, Blinding anyone in line of sight.
Grenadier_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a suppression blade. FIRE to throw. The blade sticks to the first surface it hits, winds up, and Suppresses anyone in the radius of the explosion. Enemies can destroy this blade.
Grenadier_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: EQUIP an explosive fragment. FIRE to throw. ALT FIRE to lob. The fragment sticks to the floor and explodes multiple times, dealing near lethal damage at the center with each explosion.
Grenadier_Strings.Ultimate_Description: INSTANTLY overload with polarized radianite energy that pulses from KAY/O in a massive radius. Enemies hit with pulses are Suppressed for a short duration. While overloaded, KAY/O gains Combat Stim and can be re-stabilized if downed.
Grenadier_Strings.Description: KAY/O is a machine of war built for a single purpose: neutralizing radiants. His power to Suppress enemy abilities dismantles his opponents' capacity to fight back, securing him and his allies the ultimate edge.

Guide_Strings.Ultimate_Description: EQUIP a Seeker trinket.  FIRE to send out three Seekers to track down the three closest enemies.  If a Seeker reaches its target, it Nearsights them. Enemies can destroy the Seekers.
Guide_Strings.Ability1_Description: EQUIP a Tasmanian tiger trinket. FIRE to send out and take control of the predator.  While in control, FIRE to leap forward, exploding in a Concussive blast on impact and damaging directly hit enemies.
Guide_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a hawk trinket.  FIRE to send it forward. HOLD FIRE to guide the hawk in the direction of your crosshair. RE-USE while the hawk is in flight to transform it into a flash. The flash reaches max potency after a short duration during the hawk's flight.
Guide_Strings.Ability3_Description: EQUIP a healing trinket.  HOLD FIRE to channel, Healing allies in range and line of sight.  Can be reused until her healing pool is depleted.  Skye cannot heal herself.
Guide_Strings.Description: Hailing from Australia, Skye and her band of beasts trailblaze the way through hostile territory. With her creations hampering the enemy, and her power to heal others, the team is strongest and safest by Skye's side.

Gumshoe_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a spycam. FIRE to place the spycam at the targeted location. RE-USE this ability to take control of the camera's view. While in control of the camera, FIRE to shoot a marking dart. This dart will Reveal the location of any player struck by the dart. This ability can be picked up to be REDEPLOYED.
Gumshoe_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: EQUIP a trapwire. FIRE to place a destructible and covert tripwire at the targeted location, creating a line that spans between the placed location and the wall opposite. Enemy players who cross a tripwire will be Tethered, Revealed, and Concussed after a short period if they do not destroy the device in time. This ability can be picked up to be REDEPLOYED.
Gumshoe_Strings.Ability1_Description: INSTANTLY toss the cyber cage in front of Cypher. ACTIVATE to create a zone that blocks vision and plays an audio cue when enemies pass through it
Gumshoe_Strings.Ultimate_Description: INSTANTLY use on a targeted dead enemy to download information on their team.  After a brief delay, the location of all living enemy players will be Revealed twice.

PlayerFacingPerfStrings.InputLatency_Present_Description: CPU time spent waiting on swap chain present calls (for previous frame rendering to complete).  This duration is also included in the Game Latency metric, and typically only applies in windowed mode or with VSync enabled. Framerate Limiting and NVIDIA Reflex can help to reduce this time.

PlayerFacingPerfStrings.ServerFrameRate_Description: Frames per second for the server.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.FiringErrors_Setting_Tooltip: Movement (blue) and Firing (orange) error for each shot
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.CPUBoundPercentage_Description: Percentage of recent frames bound by the CPU.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.GPUBoundPercentage_Description: Percentage of recent frames bound by the GPU.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.InputLatency_Description: Time contribution of CPU game latency and GPU render latency  to input latency.  Game to GPU Render complete latency is from the start of frame simulation to the end of GPU rendering for that frame.  Only accounts for latency from CPU and GPU processing time, not hardware latency.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.InputLatency_CPU_Description: Time contribution of CPU game latency to input latency.  Game latency is from the start of frame simulation to when the graphics driver finishes submitting work to the GPU.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.InputLatency_Description_GPU: Time contribution of GPU render latency to input latency.  Render latency is from the start ofthe render queue to when the GPU finishes rendering. Effectively the GPU contribution to system latency.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.IdleFrameTime_Description: Time spent idle each frame due to a frame limiter.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.RHIFrameTime_Description:
Time spent in the Render Hardware Interface thread each frame.
The RHI thread is responsible for issuing commands to graphics hardware when multithreaded rendering is enabled.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.CPUFrameTime_Description:
Time spent in the game thread each frame.
The game thread is responsible for updating most parts of the game simulation (ex. processing inputs, moving, shooting).
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.GPUFrameTime_Description:
Time spent in the render thread each frame.
The render thread is responsible for deciding what objects in the scene need to be rendered and issuing commands to graphics hardware (when multithreaded rendering is disabled).
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.GPURenderFrameTime_Description: Time spent on the GPU rendering each frame.
PlayerFacingPerfStrings.EndToEndLatency_Setting_Tooltip: Total latency experienced by a Client. Includes network transmission as well as Server and Client buffering delays. Only accurate in multiplayer game sessions.

Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_10:
Control. Your father had it with his mind. Radiant support technologies that make life livable for millions. A path that started with you.
 
Control. Your mother had it with her service. Transforming her community for the better, through an adherence to justice and law.
 
Control. Your mentors Ling and Zyanya have it with their power. Living examples of Radiant possibility.
 
Control. The gift so many yearn to give you. The one thing you will never have.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_3:
First Light was not kind to you, John. Or was it Fred? Everywhere I look, a new alias. Marcus. Yohan. Dimitri. But no true name. Do you even know who you were? From what I found at Point Light, I suspect not.

What sort of person has no name? Not an honest one. You are a monster now; perhaps you were a monster before.

If you succeed in finding your answer, I hope you don’t regret it.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_1:
Hello, Liam.

You keep your people close, don’t you? First the BFD, Engine 8. Then the Special Forces - you and your Ragged Ravens. You would have done anything for them.

And yet, despite all your best efforts, you watched Tariq Porter die. What did Sumaira say when you told her?

Now. After all this time, has anything changed? Or are you leading VALORANT to the slaughter? Do you really think you can save anyone?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_16:
How do you exist? Kingdom has no Anti-Yield program. It's a rejected project proposal, nothing more. But here you stand. An Anti-Yield Operative. Curious.

Regardless of origin, your purpose is clear. Kill Radiants. Yet you fight alongside them. Call them allies. Can you survive that fallacy? Does it strain your code? Isn't each directive you resist a step towards breaking down?

I have seen the way you look at Reyna. Even without eyes, the pain is written on your face.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_18:
Jamie Adeyemi. A gifted troublemaker. So much promise, so much talent, stoked into a single flame. But that fire burns hot.

You embrace it, you feed it, you revel in its brightness. But what of the kindling? A little boy from Peckham, raised by women constantly fretting for your safety. It didn’t stop you then. It doesn’t stop you, now.

So much promise. So many that love you. And you would risk it all, just to burn a little brighter.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_12:
Klara Böhringer. Distinguished Inventor Nominee. Kingdom R&D lead at 18. Zehra and Emil must have been so proud.

Perhaps you were too successful. How many breakthroughs did you hand over without thought to the implications? How many innovations did you champion, only for others to twist for a purpose you never dreamed?

Good intentions count for little. Ignorance even less. So I must ask: do you have any idea how bloody your hands truly are?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_4:
Ling Ying Wei. The Balm of Shaanxi. All the good you’ve done. The costs endured. Yes, I found the monastery.

Have you forgotten those lessons? Over and over, they taught Balance. Action, reaction. Do you believe this does not apply to you? That a life saved does not mean a life taken? I don’t know the answer. Do you? Or is the thought of it too much? That with every selfless act, your toll keeps climbing? 

Yes. Ignorance is safer.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_13:
Oh, Zyanya. You have seen painful things in your time. And you have gone to extremes in response. I have seen your sanctuary. Those people. Those children. Stolen away from Kingdom's microscope, into a community where broken things can mend. All built by you.

You cherish them, protect them, avenge them.

Yet none hold the same place in your heart as Lucia. Your own blood. The one life you may not be strong enough to save.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_7:
Sasha Novikov. The man who never missed a shot.

“Never” is a strange word. Think of the weight it carries. It’s a legacy you made before you took the name Sova. From when they called you Filin. Brother of Steel and String.

But “never” is a lie. You’ve missed your shot before. It will happen again. Despite training, despite denial, your aim will falter when it matters most. And then you must ask yourself: what was your legacy even for?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_15:
Sunwoo Han. Always on the move. Anything to keep you running. You ran after the restaurant was all but destroyed. A “freak storm,” they called it. How unusual.

You ran after Venice. Your face was everywhere: enemy of the world. A dangerous Radiant. Those who knew you were horrified. Disgusted, even. Ashamed.

You claim you are innocent - that it wasn't you. Perhaps you even believe it. But can you really outrun what people think of you?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_5:
Tayane Alves. Tatá to friends. Daughter of her beloved city.

I have walked your streets; seen your art. Beautiful, if not lacking in discipline. But the abandoned Kingdom plots remain. Splashed with paint. A testament to your victories.

That paint is fading. You’ve been away too long. Kingdom is a weed, and it will return to choke the life from your home. What will become of Bahia, I wonder, when you are indisposed?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_9:
The Torsten family was pursued and punished, but not you, Erik. Not the congenital amputee. The judge couldn't see past your disability. They insulted you with piteous lenience: unwanted, unneeded, undeserved.

So you struck back. The Stockholm Radianite Reserve.The Gothenburg Job. Your trip to Salvador. Ignoring you became impossible. Notoriety so high you had to disappear. You showed them you’re as much a Torsten as the rest.

Was the lesson worth it? Knowing now you can never go home?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_2:
The esteemed Dr. Callas.

The youngest recipient of the R. Francis Prize. Winner of the Denton Outstanding Innovation Award. And the first Chief Scientific Officer on Kingdom’s Board of Advisors.

And then… the incident. Everything changed after that, didn’t it? You changed. You isolated yourself - shed all the pieces of your life in the name of vengeance.

Have you ever stopped to think about what's left? Of the person that will remain? When all your rage is spent?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_14:
What drew you to the lake, Efia Danso? What was it you found there, at that crater more than one million years old? Not a place for a city girl like you.

Perhaps it was the night sky. Looking up, what did you see? Stars, bright and beautiful and distant? 

No. You saw the emptiness between. The impossible cold. There is so much more of it, isn’t there? So much more darkness than light.
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_6:
When did your game start, Vincent? Saint-Étienne? Culverin? Kingdom Defense was only a stepping stone - by then you had your path.

And what a path. Your ends allude me, but this is not aimless ambition. Whatever your goal, you believe it necessary. It is, perhaps, the one truth you hold sacred.

But no matter your intent - right or wrong - there will be judgment. If it goes against you, if they call you “villain”... Can you live with that forever?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_11:
You have quite the résumé, Kirra. The Nimbin Project failure. The Blue Mountains miracle. South Coast. Sawn Rocks. Kangaroo Valley. On and on.
 
Has the Great Reclaimer lost her way? You fought Kingdom for years; how is VALORANT any different? The money. The agenda. Just another corporate machine. And when they whistle, you come running. A wild beast brought to heel. 
 
Can you remain their dutiful pet? Even as the wilds wither, and your world burns?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_17:
You leave quite the trail of broken bones, don’t you, Ryo? Tokyo. Yokohama. The Ito Conglomerate. You are so dedicated to your cause. Resolute in crushing your enemies.

A loner is what they call you. A title you have worn with pride. Even as every love, every friendship, buckles under the weight of your ferocity.

But I wonder: when you have finally finished the job you set out to do, will you have anyone left to share in its end?
Range_Dossier_StringTable.Range_Dossier_Body_8:
Your safehouses are quite comfortable, Amir. The basement in Rabat. The Tangier apartment. Your lovely den in Marrakesh. Such hospitality.

Already your mind is churning. You’ll abandon these compromised locations. Start again. Hide deeper. Cease to exist.

And your face. You've considered revealing it to those closest to you, but no. Too risky. The mask stays on. Because what’s another year without Nora seeing your eyes, or sharing a smile with your little one?

Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_50_Body:
Agent 03 has deactivated their tracking hardware. 
Details follow:

Last known location: VALORANT HQ Gate: North
Time: 03:13

This is an automated message. Do not reply.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_25_Body:
Agents,

The team is now beyond our reach. Until the beacon is established they’re on their own.

That puts us in a holding pattern, and I’d like those who can to capitalize on it: agents not on active assignment are approved for time away. Please rest up and recharge. I need you ready for what’s next.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_14_Body:
Agents,
Our team sortie into Omega commences imminently. We’re bringing the battle to their turf - a first for this conflict. Take a moment and think about what that means. This is a historic event, and the danger we’ll face is equally grave. There’s no fame in it. We are ghosts to our world, but protecting it is our responsibility. So stay sharp. And good luck.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_10_Body:
Agents,
Word around headquarters travels fast, so I’ll cut to it: the recent threat to our security was a single, independent target. She was apprehended last night thanks to the efforts of our strike team in Turkey and is currently being detained. An unusual move for us, I know, but this is an unusual situation. I need all of you on high alert. We’ll have answers soon.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_11_Body:
Brimstone, with all due respect: are you CRAZY?? This lady terrorizes us for weeks and then you offer her a job?

Cypher said she didn’t know about Omega. Okay, fine. But do you really expect us to trust her after, you know, the literal blackmail? I get that she’s a stone-cold hardass, but can we put recruiting to a vote next time?
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_2_Body:
Chamber’s history is as he claims: French military, then made a name for himself as a PMC marksman. Moved to Kingdom weapons design after. At present, Killjoy validated the portal blueprints he provided, so his source is sound.
He has no criminal record. No incident reports. Either his reputation is perfect, or he’s very good at hiding the truth. You know where I stand.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_26_Body:
Forgive the brevity, this situation in Omega needs close attention. Astra’s working to understand the repercussions. So far the original fears of an Alpha impact have not been realized, but we’re monitoring. The on-site team deserves major recognition. Their rapid response may have spared us the worst.


You all want answers, and so do I, but this may take some time.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_56_Body:
Great news, Brimstone - we found what we've been looking for! It just looked like a nondescript islet from satellites, but our sensors uncovered a sizable subterranean space with - as Clove put it - "ma-hoosive" power readings.

I don't think they're aware of us, but either way... we should move fast. Speed is of the essence, and all that, yes?

KJ
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_39_Body: Have you lost your mind?! I am not shutting down a critical Kingdom facility! I asked you for a little help with some intel, and you gave me nothing. Now you want me to trash my reputation. After everything we’ve been through. Everything we’ve done for each other, I can’t believe this is where you go, Liam. Don’t contact me again.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_18_Body: Hazal Eyletmez, it's been a long time. I wish we could correspond under better circumstances. Operative Batra is no longer employed with REALM. He is a fugitive under investigation for the theft of a priceless artifact. I’ve told you this much as a professional courtesy. Whoever you're working for, tell them this is an internal matter. Do not inquire further.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_29_Body: Hey Boss. A pal in Los Angeles sent me his Gochujang recipe. He mentioned his restaurant had lost the dinner crowd. His whole neighborhood is lockin’ their doors. They’re freaked out by reports of weird things spotted near a Kingdom Facility. Maybe Fade’s nightmares have me spooked. But I’m going to Cali for some in-person recon. Jett, out.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_12_Body:
Hey Brim! Wonderful news: our terminal works! I’m delighted to say that it did NOT shred Fade into tiny little pieces on her test trip to Omega. We can use it for a fully staffed mission - just say the word.

Before I forget: the transponder picked up a second portal location in the city. Fade felt something nearby. Something big. Might be worth a look.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_15_Body:
How did we not know any of this? The soldiers. That garden. And now this crisis of conscience? No, unacceptable. But let's start here: moving forward, Neon also trains with me. Limiting emotion does not work, she must use it. If Sage won't teach her that, I will.

Your radianite is stockpiled with our new friends. I suggest you find out who they are.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_3_Body:
I agree. If we are to welcome additional recruits like the one you describe, we need to formalize Radiant training as part of our process. Reyna will want to lead the program. This is a mistake. Her philosophies are too dangerous for new recruits.

I would be honored to helm this effort. I have already started work on a proposal.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_43_Body: I analyzed Sova’s scans of Kingdom West but found no hint of Omega Particles. If agents of Legion or Atlas had been on site, traces would be everywhere. So based on the science, I can rule out Omega Earth’s involvement. There was something weird in the security circuits. A residual image from an intruder’s jamming technology? Raze thinks it looks like an hourglass.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_45_Body: I got a hit. A hitman, to be precise. He’s willing to cooperate but wants protection from his former employer. We certainly excel at making ourselves disappear. This assassin is our best lead on uncovering the fate of those missing scientists. But his dark web trail is too clean. It's as if he wanted to be found. What do you think, boss? Should I set up a rendezvous and extraction?
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_9_Body:
I had something of a breakthrough with those encrypted messages from our dear blackmailer. The exact origin point is still unknown. But it came from somewhere in Turkey. Of this I am certain.

Now you must answer the question: what will you do when we find this person? Your conscience is too troublesome for an execution. But what alternatives there are, I do not know.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_40_Body:
I know how hard this next part is going to be for you. You never wanted it to come to this. I’m sorry that it did. When it’s done, you’ll pick up the pieces and fix it. You always do.

I’m here if you want to talk. You don't have to bear this alone.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_54_Body:
I met with Omen. We spoke at length, and I noted some immediate points I think we can act on. Most importantly, we should leave him alone.

His trust in us has been deeply shaken. Understandably so. He has promised to contact us when he uncovers more information, but right now, I want to let him work, heal, and be alone.

I'll see you soon.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_8_Body:
I told you not to test me.

Do you think I am blind to the coming and going of your little scouts? Sova will not find me. And neither will Cypher. All you have done is waste my time. If you cannot prove your innocence, I will hand over your data to the public. This is just the beginning.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_7_Body:
I tracked down our leads but did not find the blackmailer. Cypher claims the message encryption is untraceable, so for now we must search the old way. 

There has been no further word from this person, yes? Hard to say if that is good or ill. I will keep searching.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_4_Body:
I'll be slipping away between missions for a while. There are consequences to building this bridge between worlds. I must see to those now so that our ripples do not become waves.

We will speak when I return. Be safe, chale.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_51_Body:
I've completed my breakdown review of the Outlaw, and I have to say... I'm impressed. I always admire attempts at the unconventional, and a sniper rifle with an over-under layout, each with integrated muzzle brakes? It certainly fits the bill.

I'll send over the full report soon. Needless to say, Bulwark have impressed me.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_37_Body:
Is it normal for Kingdom to contract external vendors, even as specialized as The Vault? Regardless, the failed shipment signals an effort to consolidate the work in-house. Svalbard's capture process was prototype only. And if there’s one thing Kingdom can do on their own, it’s scale.

We meet with Deadlock again this afternoon. I am anxious to learn more from her about this so-called interverse.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_48_Body: Iso reached out because he needs help. And I need answers. Working together is our best chance at learning more about the organization that controlled him, forcing him to be a killer. Look at the intel we gathered on the target. Let me pursue this. Order the raid. Whatever happens, my family is VALORANT. You have my word.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_5_Body:
Italy's back on the conspiracy sites. New surveillance shots of Phoenix and Jett from last year. Cypher's scrubbing them now. 

Also, families of the Everett-Linde team are asking Kingdom questions. I told you this would happen. If we don't lay low, VP won't be a secret much longer.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_33_Body: It’s time we reevaluate radiant classifications. Our rigid definitions don’t reflect the spectrum. It is easy with children of First Light. But how to account for Astra? Yoru? What of Harbor, whose powers stem from the artifact itself? We have discussed Omen’s situation at length. And now Gekko. His account of the creature bonding process contradicts our every assumption. So much we don’t know. Thoughts?
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_42_Body: I’ve been monitoring Kingdom’s response in the aftermath of Los Angeles. K-SEC’s internal reports indicate Landfall team leadership has gone missing. There’s no evidence these scientists were lost in the portal explosion. There’s something else going on here. Is it Legion? Atlas? Or could it be a new enemy from Omega Earth? I’ll keep hunting.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_46_Body:
I’ve completed my assessment of Iso’s Radiant power. He manipulates the structure of Radianite itself, transmuting it from intangible energy into solid form. Like water changing states with a shift in temperature.

The “arena,” as he calls it, is remarkable in and of itself. To construct a stabilized reality inside the Interverse? He is an architect - in the truest sense of the word.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_16_Body:
Killjoy's download gave me a back door to security schedules and maintenance windows. With caution, we’ll preserve our access to Omega through the second gate.

Our counterparts have clearly been busy. It's too early for an official report, but there is preliminary evidence that they've obtained a new power source of some kind. We are looking into it.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_35_Body:
Liam! It’s been ages, man. You’re about to drop off the old leaderboard. Swing by HQ, show the puppies how an old dog runs CQB. Unless private sector consulting’s slowed you down, haha.

I could actually use your help. We got looted, proprietary goods went walkies. Got any leads for an old partner? I know you’re not fully out of the game. KSEC for life!
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_13_Body:
Monsieur: I was wrong about the limiter release for Neon’s suit. I suggested we adjust her voltage caps. A dangerous error. Her power is greater than I first projected, so I have apologized. But my words fall on deaf ears.

To other matters. Our work to reverse engineer Omega’s Spike moves apace. Killjoy will have a prototype in a matter of days. Le vent tourne.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_44_Body: My sessions with Fade and Sage have proven fruitless. My memory of the hourglass symbol has not returned. But I swear I have seen it before. I have already spoken to Cypher and will say the same to you: keep me informed as you learn more. My past has been a mystery for too long, Brimstone.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_21_Body:
My team recovered a discarded communicator whose logs indicate that the fugitive has recently been in contact with an unknown entity. I think it was you.

I said it before and I'll say it again: Varun Batra is none of your business. Stay out of REALM affairs.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_28_Body: Nobody has Eelpouts! I wanted the fish as a funny gift for Raze, but everyone is sold out. I tried to buy her a microorganism, but they’re gone too! I checked the supply chain; the buyer’s a hazmat reserve company contracted with Kingdom. What are they researching and developing with cute creatures that thrive near volatile forces? Why hide it? Fishy, no?
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_31_Body: Nobody who saw Gekko’s creatures is talking. Cypher confirmed the lack of incriminating surveillance video. To be safe, he coded a worm to hunt online footage. K-Sec has no clue where to find their stolen property. Or the thief’s identity. I’ll talk to Gekko about being more covert. We got away with it this time, Brimstone. But you know K-Sec. They’ll never stop looking.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_6_Body:
Now to discover who you really are. If it was you that took him, I will pull your precious Valorant out of the darkness and lay bare your secrets. You are not as shadowed as you believe. 

Do not test me.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_52_Body:
Omen brought our new friend, as promised. They are smart, intuitive, and certainly fearless. I'll drill them on firearms until they're mission ready.

Re: Omen, I tried to talk with him after the handover, but he wouldn't speak, and left as soon as we were done. Still, the fact that he's cooperating means something, yes? I suggest we exercise patience.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_47_Body: Omen is unstable. His obsession with Iso is more than a distraction; it’s a clear and present danger to VALORANT. What if a return of memories triggers an episode? We don’t truly know what Omen’s capable of. And there is too much we don’t know about Iso. We can’t risk putting these two in the same room. Do not disregard my concerns.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_34_Body: Omen was after me about Max Bot going off program. Now he thinks I’m jacking VLT/R fuel? Those chemicals are too unstable, even for my toys. Where’s the trust, man? When Fade hacked our personnel files, did Omen get a look? My past isn’t perfect, Chefinho. But honesty is my vibe. Did I tell you KJ and I took Harbor’s bike on a joyride?
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_23_Body: Public sightings of Legion are down. They’re mobilizing. It has to be this lost city. Its purpose is unclear - too many credible theories. First Light’s the real complication, though; post divide, there’s no way to guess the sites’ interplay. But Legion can’t know either, they’re gambling. And that concerns me.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_19_Body:
REALM is making the news now. Batra keeps escaping, they must be pissed. Word from the media coverage only points two ways: Radiant, or Radianite. What if this stolen artifact is like my mask? It could explain a lot.

Cypher says there’s no REALM in Omega. Only here in Alpha. These worlds keep drifting further apart.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_41_Body:
Respectfully, sir, you did not betray anyone. Today you protected Kingdom from itself. It won’t be the last time either. It’s time to make peace with that. 

Project Landfall is abandoned. No radivore invasion. Legion repelled. Your team survived. This was a good day.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_49_Body:
Team 2 confirms the skyrise has already been abandoned. No bodies. No survivors. The artifacts Omen described are gone. These Scions of Hourglass clearly do not wish to be found. And here I thought we were the covert ones.

Finding more of these assassin cells may prove difficult. But if this group knew about Radianite before its modern rediscovery, I doubt we have a choice.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_32_Body: Thanks for approving my sprint back to Taguig! It’s more than a homecoming. KJ and Reyna designed a new capacitor to help me control my pack’s limiter. They offered to do the install, but I get nervous when my conduction cells are involved. Who better to upgrade the rig than the man who designed it? Back soon, boss! Bye-bye!
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_22_Body:
The accounts are purged. Greaves cannot follow Varun further, and our anonymity is preserved. What Greaves does next, I cannot say. I suspect we'll see little of him. For now. But silence and stillness are not the same. He conceals a trail of his own.

Also: Skye recovered Varun's bike. That should buy us some good will.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_17_Body:
The keeper of Legion's new power source has a name: Varun Batra. I ran a trace on his Alpha counterpart. Turns out he’s a REALM operative. I freelanced for REALM years ago; multinational task force recovering historical artifacts from black market trade. My first question: why does Legion need an antiquities expert?

I haven’t spoken to REALM in ages, but I’ll put you in touch.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_20_Body: The more we dig into Batra, the less I take him for a criminal. Besides this theft, his record’s spotless. But REALM is just as sterling. Busting black market operations? Returning confiscated antiquities to their origin countries? That’s one noble mission statement. They wouldn’t hunt an innocent man. We don’t have the whole truth. I know it.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_53_Body:
The new kid and I have been poring over this journal, but I'm not at all familiar with these encryption techniques the Scions use. I'm going to pull Harbor in and see if he's seen any of this during his time at REALM. They dealt with artifacts - maybe the Scions and REALM crossed paths without Harbor ever realising it.

I'm reaching. I know.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_24_Body:
The new teleportal compact is ready. Astra, Skye, and Harbor enjoyed a full demonstration. Once they reach the city, they’ll deploy the tech and we’ll have access. They’ve also been equipped with cross-dimensional comm arrays, though we are less certain of their reliability. Let’s not fret prematurely if the team goes dark.

Good luck to our travelers.
Range_Email_StringTable.Jam_Atlas_Dossier_1_Body:
The team has arrived. Setup is on track to conclude within the hour. Our presence is being kept to a minimum per orders.

We have received the Legion Ambassador’s report of the latest encounter. I suspect information was omitted. I will conduct our own investigation and submit our findings.

My team is mission briefed. Any Alpha presence detection will be reported immediately.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_38_Body: The time has come to heed Deadlock’s warning. It won’t matter if those arrogant fools started with good intentions if the results are catastrophic. Your K-Sec contact opened the back door for diplomacy. Without revealing VALORANT, you need to make him understand what’s at stake. If Kingdom refuses to take that facility offline, we will be ready to pull the plug.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_55_Body:
We figured out some COORDINATES! Me and Cypher are gonna check out these wee islands in the middle of nowhere. Also, Harbor and Astra are heading to Lotus for energy signatures or something. Don't ask me.

Last thing... I borrowed Deadlock's jacket. Because I'm off up north and I didn't pack properly. I told her you said it was grand. So thanks! Bye! Good luck!
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_1_Body:
We finished the Everett-Linde sweep. Nothing on the teleportal. Cypher's trying one last data recovery, but I'm not holding my breath.
Without blueprints, reverse engineering will take time we don't have. It's a full Alpha-Omega bridge. Kingdom's short-range ports give Killjoy a baseline to work from, but this is another level.
Makes you wonder what else Omega's got.

-V
Range_Email_StringTable.Jam_Atlas_Dossier_2_Body:
We have determined the scorch marks on the floor of the primary structure to indeed be new. We’re looking into their source. Residual energy readings don’t match the database. Samples for analysis will be collected and ready for transport by next resupply.

I request that an unredacted version of Legion’s original report be obtained by any available channels.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_30_Body: Welcome to VALORANT, kid. While Sage and KJ play zookeeper, Harbor says your training room scores are high. Some tricks from this old dog. Skip the run and gun. Stop, head-lock, and pop-pop. But mind the recoil. Coordinate action with your team by memorizing Cypher’s maps. And don’t hesitate to communicate. My Agents can talk a lot of trash, but they all want the win!
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_36_Body:
You wouldn’t believe what I hear these Kingdom employees talking about in line at the truck. No filter when you’re hungry I guess. I added some new menu items; the bulgogi torta was a hit. Today I overheard some goofballs chatting about cargo pickups in Norway, and something about “rad or four.” Look into it?

Shoot more customers at the window gotta go.
Range_Email_StringTable.Range_Email_27_Body:
Your revisions are adequate.

Can we consider this done? Frankly we’ve wasted too much time on paperwork. If agents choose to risk personal attachment to each other, so be it. They’re adults. They’ll do what they want. We can spare them this sacrifice.

If that’s all, I have actual work to do.

Rift_StringTable.Ability_Passive_Description: ACTIVATE Ultimate to enter Astral Form and PRIMARY FIRE to place Stars. Target Stars with your Nova Pulse, Nebula, or Gravity Well to use those abilities.
Rift_StringTable.Ability_X_Description:
ACTIVATE to enter Astral Form where you can place Stars with FIRE. Stars can be reactivated later, transforming them into a Nova Pulse, Nebula, or Gravity Well.

When Cosmic Divide is charged, use ALT FIRE in Astral Form to begin aiming it, then FIRE to select two locations. An infinite Cosmic Divide connects the two points you select. Cosmic Divide blocks bullets and sound.
Rift_StringTable.PlaceRiftFailure_TooClose: CANNOT PLACE TEAR CLOSE TO EXISTING TEAR
Rift_StringTable.Description: Ghanaian Agent Astra harnesses the energies of the cosmos to reshape battlefields to her whim. With full command of her astral form and a talent for deep strategic foresight, she's always eons ahead of her enemy's next move.
Rift_StringTable.Ability_Q_Description:
Place Stars in Astral Form (Ultimate Key).

ACTIVATE a Star to detonate a Nova Pulse. The Nova Pulse charges briefly then strikes, Concussing all players in its area.
Rift_StringTable.Ability_C_Description:
Place Stars in Astral Form (Ultimate Key).

ACTIVATE a Star to form a Gravity Well. Players in the area are pulled toward the center before it explodes, making all players still trapped inside Vulnerable.
Rift_StringTable.Ability_4_Description:
Place Stars in Astral Form (Ultimate Key). 

ACTIVATE a Star to transform it into a Nebula (smoke).

USE a Star to Dissipate it, returning the Star to be placed in a new location after a delay.

Dissipate briefly forms a fake Nebula at the Star's location before returning.

RunItBack2_StringTable.RunItBack2_Bundle_Store_Description_AllC: CELEBRATE THE NEW YEAR WITH A HAND-PICKED SELECTION OF SOME OF OUR FAVORITE SKINS FROM 2021.
RunItBack2_StringTable.RunItBack2_Bundle_Store_Description: Celebrate the new year with a hand-picked selection of some of our favorite skins from 2021.

RunItBack_E77_StringTable.RunItBackEp7_Bundle_Store_Description: Celebrate the new year with a hand-picked selection of some of our favorite skins from 2023.

Sandbox_Strings.Ability1_Description: EQUIP a sphere of shielding water. FIRE to throw. ALT FIRE to lob. Upon impacting the ground, spawn a destructible water shield that blocks bullets.
Sandbox_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a wall of water. FIRE to send the water forward along the ground. HOLD FIRE to guide the water in the direction of your crosshair, passing through the world, spawning a wall along the water’s path. ALT FIRE while bending to stop the water early. Players hit are Slowed.
Sandbox_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: EQUIP a wave of water. FIRE to send the wave rolling forward and through walls. RE-USE to stop the wave. Players hit are Slowed.
Sandbox_Strings.Ultimate_Description: EQUIP the full power of your Artifact. FIRE to summon a geyser pool on the ground. Enemy players in the area are targeted by successive geyser strikes. Players caught within a strike are Concussed.
Sandbox_Strings.Description: Hailing from India’s coast, Harbor storms the field wielding ancient technology with dominion over water. He unleashes frothing rapids and crushing waves to shield his allies, or pummel those that oppose him.

Sarge_Strings.Ultimate_Description: EQUIP a tactical map. FIRE to launch a lingering orbital strike laser at the selected location, dealing high damage-over-time to players caught in the selected area.
Sarge_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a tactical map. FIRE to set locations where Brimstone's smoke clouds will land. ALT FIRE to confirm, launching long-lasting smoke clouds that block vision in the selected area.
Sarge_Strings.Ability1_Description: EQUIP an incendiary grenade launcher. FIRE to launch a grenade that detonates as it comes to a rest on the floor, creating a lingering fire zone that damages players within the zone.
Sarge_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: INSTANTLY toss down a stim beacon. Upon landing, it creates a field that grants players a Combat Stim and a Speed Boost.
Sarge_Strings.Description: Joining from the U.S.A., Brimstone's orbital arsenal ensures his squad always has the advantage. His ability to deliver utility precisely and safely make him the unmatched boots-on-the-ground commander.

Sequoia_StringTable.Description: Chinese fixer for hire Iso falls into a flow state to dismantle the opposition. Reconfiguring ambient energy into bulletproof protection, he advances with focus towards his next duel to the death.
Sequoia_StringTable.Ability_Q_Description: EQUIP a molecular bolt. FIRE to throw it forward, briefly applying Vulnerable to all players it touches. The bolt can pass through solid objects, including walls.
Sequoia_StringTable.Ability_X_Description: EQUIP an interdimensional arena. FIRE to hurl a column of energy through the battlefield, pulling you and the first enemy hit into the arena. You and your opponent duel to the death.
Sequoia_StringTable.Ability_4_Description: EQUIP to assemble prismatic energy. FIRE to push an indestructible wall of energy forward that blocks bullets.
Sequoia_StringTable.Ability_E_Description: START a focus timer. Once completed, enter a flow state during which downed enemies you kill or damage generate an energy orb. Shooting this orb grants you a shield which absorbs one instance of damage from any source.

ShootinRange_Strings.OpenRangeDescription: A never ending supply of flying drones in an open air shooting range. Experiment with weapons and abilities freely with space to stretch your legs.
ShootinRange_Strings.OpenRangeDescriptionShort: Freely explore the entire range and all it has to offer.
ShootinRange_Strings.DefuseRetakeDescription: In this exercise use your tools to take out all bots defending the planted Spike. Maximize abilities and gun skills to methodically clear the site, defeat the bots and make sure you leave enough time to defuse the Spike!
ShootinRange_Strings.DefuseRetakeDescriptionShort: Methodically defeat enemies and defuse the Spike before time runs out!
ShootinRange_Strings.AdaptiveSkillTestDescription:
Shoot each target as it appears.
Targets are defeated in 1 headshot or 4 body shots.
Targets disappear after a set duration,
determined by the current difficulty level.
Difficulty increases with eliminations
and decreases after with misses.
ShootinRange_Strings.DanceHallUserInfoDescription:
Shoot each target as it appears.
Targets die in 1 headshot or 4 body shots.
Eight sets of four targets.
Difficulty will scale based on performance.
ShootinRange_Strings.TimedSkillTestDescription:
Shoot each target as it appears.
Targets die in 1 headshot or 4 body shots.
Eliminate as many targets as you can in 30 seconds.
ShootinRange_Strings.PlantDefendDescriptionShort: Take control of the site, plant the Spike, and defend it until detonation.
ShootinRange_Strings.PlantDefendDescription:
Take over the site, clear out the defending bots, and plant the Spike.

Make sure you have enough left in you to defend the Spike from an additional wave of bots who are trying to defuse it!
ShootinRange_Strings.SkillTestDescription: Test your gun skills with a variety of different shooting challenges. Go for a time challenge or mow down waves of bots using different guns and abilities.
ShootinRange_Strings.SkillTestDescriptionShort: Test your gun skills with a variety of shooting challenges.
ShootinRange_Strings.ShootingRangeEntryDescription:
The range allows you to try out different agents, guns and abilities in a controlled environment with no time constraints. Move around and discover the various exercises and challenges you can enter to practice your skills.

Check out how movement, crouching and aiming down sights impacts your accuracy and how different guns have different characteristics. Discover how guns and agents differ across a variety of scenarios.
ShootinRange_Strings.Launch_Range_PartyAdvisory: YOU WILL REMAIN IN YOUR CURRENT PARTY.
ShootinRange_Strings.ShootingRangeControlsDescription: You can swap agents at any time you see the prompt on your screen by pressing the F2 key. All agents are unlocked in the range!

Sprinter_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: FIRE two energy lines forward on the ground that extend a short distance or until they hit a surface. The lines rise into walls of static electricity that block vision.
Sprinter_Strings.Description: Filipino Agent Neon surges forward at shocking speeds, discharging bursts of bioelectric radiance as fast as her body generates it. She races ahead to catch enemies off guard then strikes them down quicker than lightning.
Sprinter_Strings.Ability2_Description: INSTANTLY channel Neon’s power for Increased Speed. When charged, ALT FIRE to trigger an electric slide. Slide charge resets every two kills.
Sprinter_Strings.Ability1_Description: INSTANTLY throw an energy bolt that bounces once. Upon hitting each surface, the bolt electrifies the ground below with a Concussive blast.
Sprinter_Strings.Ultimate_Description: Unleash Neon’s full power and speed for a short duration. FIRE to channel the power into a deadly lightning beam with high movement accuracy.

Stealth_Strings.Ultimate_Description: EQUIP a mask that can see between dimensions. FIRE to drift into Yoru's dimension, unable to be affected or seen by enemies from the outside. REACTIVATE to exit Yoru's dimension early.
Stealth_Strings.Ability2_Description: EQUIP a rift tether FIRE to send the tether forward. ALT FIRE to place a stationary tether. ACTIVATE to teleport to the tether's location. USE to trigger a fake teleport.
Stealth_Strings.GrenadeAbility_Description: EQUIP an echo that transforms into a mirror image of Yoru when activated. FIRE to instantly activate the mirror image and send it forward. ALT FIRE to place an inactive echo. USE to transform an inactive echo into a mirror image and send it forward.  Mirror images explode in a Blinding flash when destroyed by enemies.
Stealth_Strings.Ability1_Description: EQUIP to rip an unstable dimensional fragment from reality. FIRE to throw the fragment, activating a flash that winds up once it collides with a hard surface.
Stealth_Strings.Description: Japanese native Yoru rips holes straight through reality to infiltrate enemy lines unseen. Using deception and aggression in equal measure, he gets the drop on each target before they know where to look.
